   "body" : "When building the Android dependencies and `SOURCES_PATH` is set to a non-default location (i.e. not in the depends directory), doing `make apk` results in the following error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfind: â../depends/sources/â: No such file or directory\r\nfind: â../depends/sources/â: No such file or directory\r\ntar: --exclude=*/*: Cannot open: No such file or directory\r\ntar: Error is not recoverable: exiting now\r\nfind: â../depends/sources/â: No such file or directory\r\nfind: â../depends/sources/â: No such file or directory\r\ntar: --exclude=*/*: Cannot open: No such file or directory\r\ntar: Error is not recoverable: exiting now\r\nfind: â../depends/sources/â: No such file or directory\r\nfind: â../depends/sources/â: No such file or directory\r\ntar: --exclude=*/*: Cannot open: No such file or directory\r\ntar: Error is not recoverable: exiting now\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt seems like the culprit is https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/a3791da0e80ab35e862989373f033e5be4dff26b/src/Makefile.qt.include#L385-L387 which is looking for files in the default depends sources path.",
